content_chunks.content: This e-course provides an in-depth understanding of ultrasonic testing (UT) techniques for evaluating the integrity and quality of building materials. It covers fundamental principles of ultrasonic waves, testing methods, equipment, data interpretation, and practical applications in construction and civil engineering. Participants will gain knowledge about detecting defects, assessing material properties, and ensuring structural safety using UT methods. The course includes theoretical concepts, case studies, and hands-on demonstrations using virtual simulations, including examples of characterization and defect assessment in External Thermal Insulation Composite Systems (ETICS).

Ultrasonic testing technology for building material integrity assessment - this course delivers comprehensive non-destructive testing methodologies for evaluating structural safety and material quality in construction applications. Technology for defect detection includes advanced ultrasonic wave propagation analysis and wave reflection/refraction techniques for precise flaw identification in building materials. The course introduces contact testing methods and immersion testing techniques for diverse material evaluation scenarios, alongside pulse-echo testing and phased array ultrasonics for detailed structural analysis. Participants gain expertise in UT equipment calibration procedures, signal processing methodologies, and defect characterization techniques for comprehensive material assessment. The curriculum covers A-scan B-scan C-scan imaging systems, structural health monitoring applications, and specialized testing for External Thermal Insulation Composite Systems (ETICS). Students develop skills in concrete quality control protocols, steel structure inspection procedures, crack detection methodologies, and void detection techniques for ensuring construction safety. The course prepares professionals to implement advanced ultrasonic testing systems for quality assurance, maintenance planning, and structural integrity verification in both new construction and existing building assessment projects.

content_chunks.title: Introduction to UT: basics of NDT, overview of ultrasonic testing and its role in construction, applications of UT in building materials

Principles of ultrasonic wave propagation: wave propagation in solids, types of ultrasonic waves and their properties, reflection, refraction, and attenuation, factors affecting ultrasonic wave behavior
Ultrasonic testing methods and equipment: contact vs. immersion testing, pulse-echo and through-transmission techniques, phased array UT and time-of-flight diffraction, equipment and probe selection

Data acquisition and interpretation: calibration of UT equipment, signal processing and defect characterization, interpretation of A-scan, B-scan and C-scan images, case studies of defect detection in construction materials

Applications in construction and structural health monitoring: quality control of concrete and steel structures, detection of cracks, voids and delaminations, UT of bridges, tunnels, limitations and challenges of UT in construction
Hands-on virtual simulations and case studies: (interactive virtual) lab on ultrasonic equipment handling, analysis of real world case studies, group discussion and problem-solving exercises
Final assessment and course review: review of key concepts and techniques, discussion on emerging trends in ultrasonic testing, final online examination and feedback session
